ENTRY            14864   20260226   20260508   20260508       1528
SUBENT        14864001   20260226   20260508   20260508       1528
BIB                  9         18
TITLE      The Production of N16 and N17 in the Cooling Water of
           the NRX Reactor
AUTHOR     (W.J.Henderson,P.R.Tunnicliffe)
REFERENCE  (J,NSE,3,145,1958)
           #doi:10.13182/NSE58-A25456
REL-REF    (R,14134001,N.Nereson,J,PR,85,600,1952) 235U fission
           spectrum.
INSTITUTE  (1CANCRC)
FACILITY   (REAC,1CANCRC) NRX reactor.
INC-SPECT  The analytical expression for the fission spectrum
           N(E) = 0.484*exp(-E)*sinh(2E)**(0.5) is given by
           Nereson.
METHOD     (ACTIV) A continuously flowing sample of effluent
           cooling water was obtained from the bottom of an NRX
           fuelrod assembly. Detectors either for the gamma
           radiation from N16 or for the fast neutrons from N17
           were placed on the axis of the tank.
HISTORY    (20260226C) BP
ENDBIB              18
COMMON               1          3
KT-DUMMY
MEV
       1.32
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           25
SUBENT        14864002   20260226   20260508   20260508       1528
BIB                  7         14
REACTION   (8-O-16(N,P)7-N-16,,SIG,,FIS)
REL-REF    (A,11390002,H.C.Martin,J,PR,93,498,1954)
DETECTOR   (GEMUC) The detector for the gamma radiation from N16
           was a Victoreen dosimeter.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) The error quoted is derived from
           the consistency of the measurements and allowing a
           0.5-sec uncertainty in the decay time but does not
           take into account uncertainties in the conversion
           factors used.
CORRECTION Corrected for the 18 % of the N16 disintegrations
           which go to the ground state and also for decay
           during transit from the reactor to the tank.
DECAY-DATA (7-N-16,7.4SEC)
